          "date": "2015-03-25 16:17:02.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1026 ldiskfs: make bg RO if bitmaps validations fail",
        "message": "LU-1026 ldiskfs: make bg RO if bitmaps validations fail\n\nbackport following commits from upstream:\n\n48d9eb97dc74d2446bcc3630c8e51d2afc9b951d\next4: error out if verifying the block bitmap fails\n\ndbde0abed8c6e9e938c2194675ce63f5769b0d37\next4: fix type declaration of ext4_validate_block_bitmap\n\n163a203ddb36c36d4a1c942aececda0cc8d06aa7\next4: mark block group as corrupt on block bitmap error\n\n87a39389be3e3b007d341be510a7e4a0542bdf05\next4: mark block group as corrupt on inode bitmap error\n\nSince we could skip corrupt block groups, this patch\naslo use ext4_warning() intead of ext4_error()\nto make FS not remount RO in default.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I0ff2b3f15658180ec20c2a3f557829fed481f81b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
